# CSS Styling

Modern CSS offers multiple approaches to styling components. Tailwind CSS v4 is the recommended default for utility-first styling. CSS Modules provide scoped styles when you need traditional CSS. Responsive design, Flexbox, Grid, and animations are core CSS skills.

## Tailwind CSS

Tailwind provides utility classes that map directly to CSS properties. Version 4 uses a CSS-first configuration:

```tsx
export function Card({ title, children }: CardProps) {
  return (
    <div className="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm dark:border-gray-700 dark:bg-gray-800">
      <h2 className="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
        {title}
      </h2>
      <div className="mt-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
        {children}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

Tailwind v4 features:
- **CSS-first config** — configure in `app.css` with `@theme` instead of `tailwind.config.js`
- **Automatic content detection** — no need to specify content paths
- **Container queries** — `@container` support built in
- **Dark mode** — `dark:` variant uses `prefers-color-scheme` by default

## CSS Modules

CSS Modules scope class names to the component, preventing global conflicts:

```css
/* Button.module.css */
.button {
  padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
  border-radius: 0.375rem;
  font-weight: 600;
}
.primary {
  background-color: #3b82f6;
  color: white;
}
```

```tsx
import styles from "./Button.module.css";

export function Button({ variant, children }: ButtonProps) {
  return (
    <button className={`${styles.button} ${styles[variant]}`}>
      {children}
    </button>
  );
}
```

Vite and Next.js support CSS Modules out of the box. See [[frontend/bundling#vite]] for configuration.

## Responsive Design

Use Tailwind responsive prefixes or CSS media queries:

```tsx
{/* Mobile-first: stack on small screens, side-by-side on medium+ */}
<div className="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4">
  <aside className="w-full md:w-64">Sidebar</aside>
  <main className="flex-1">Content</main>
</div>
```

Breakpoints: `sm` (640px), `md` (768px), `lg` (1024px), `xl` (1280px), `2xl` (1536px).

Container queries scope responsive rules to a parent container rather than the viewport — ideal for reusable components.

## Flexbox and Grid

| Layout | Use Case |
|--------|----------|
| Flexbox | One-dimensional layouts (rows or columns), alignment, spacing |
| Grid | Two-dimensional layouts, complex page structures, equal-height cards |

```css
/* Flexbox: center content */
.container { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; }

/* Grid: responsive card grid */
.grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem; }
```

## Animations

CSS transitions for simple state changes, keyframe animations for complex sequences:

```css
/* Transition */
.button { transition: background-color 150ms ease-in-out, transform 150ms ease-in-out; }
.button:hover { background-color: #2563eb; transform: scale(1.02); }

/* Keyframe animation */
@keyframes fadeIn {
  from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(8px); }
  to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
}
.card { animation: fadeIn 200ms ease-out; }
```

Tailwind includes animation utilities: `animate-spin`, `animate-pulse`, `animate-bounce`, `animate-ping`. Use `motion-safe:` variant to respect `prefers-reduced-motion` for [[frontend/accessibility]].
